# Workflow and quality

- Prefer diagnosis before fixes unless the user explicitly asks for direct implementation.
- A code review must be systematic and cover all files in the pull request.
- During review, findings must be written to a Markdown report file.
- Keep pull requests small and easy to review; target a maximum of about 500 changed lines.
- Lint and format code according to the project setup before committing.
- For new functionality, clarify feature-flag usage in environment variables early.
